&= 8s^2 - 2s^2 \cos \theta.
\end{align*}Since $2s^2 \cos^2 \theta = 2s^2 - r^2,$
\[8s^2 - 2s^2 \cos \theta = 8s^2 - (2s^2 - r^2) = r^2 + 6s^2 = \boxed{677}.\]

